Henricus is the '''Lord Inquisitioner''', which means that he leads the [[Inquisition]]. He sells the [[Blessing of the Inquisition]] after completing [[The Inquisition Quest]].<br />
Henricus is an [[Allusions#Henricus Institoris|allusion]] to [[wikipedia:Henricus Institoris|Henricus Institoris]], one of the most prominent Inquisitioners of the 15th century.
{{JSpoiler|Main [[NPC]] of [[The Inquisition Quest]].}}

Julius is an inhabitant of [[Yalahar]]. He fears Yalahar is under threat and is looking for help.
<br />
{{JSpoiler|You need talk to him in the [[Blood Brothers Quest]].}}

'''Kevin Postner''' is the Postmaster General of the Tibian Postal Service.  His name is an obvious pun on that of the actor [[Wikipedia:Kevin Costner|Kevin Costner]] who played the title character in the 1997 film ''[[Wikipedia:The Postman|The Postman]]''.

{{JSpoiler|Main NPC of [[The Postman Missions Quest]].}}

Kevin does not sell [[letter]]s or [[parcel]]s.  For that you will have to speak to his assistant [[Wally]] downstairs.

This NPC can appear in 3 different locations depending on the most voted boss of the [[Rathleton Quest]]. She will grant you permission to fight the boss.

* When [[Bullwark]] is active, she will be on the [[Oramond Minotaur Camp|Minotaur Camp]], {{Mapper Coords|131.167|124.112|7|4|text=here}}
* When the [[Glooth Fairy]] is active, she can be found under the [[Rathleton New Sewers|New Sewers]], {{Mapper Coords|131.118|124.198|9|4|text=here}}
* When [[Lisa]] is active, she will be under the [[Rathleton Ancient Sewers|Ancient Sewers]], {{Mapper Coords|131.22|124.169|8|4|text=here}}

Captain Bluebear will transport any [[premium]] players by ship to:
{{Transport |Ab'Dendriel, 130 |Carlin, 110 |Edron, 160 |Liberty Bay, 180 |Port Hope, 160 |Roshamuul, 210 |Oramond, 150 |Svargrond, 180 |Venore, 170 |Yalahar, 200}}

He can also transport anyone to the [[Character World Transfer|world transfer]] island [[Travora]] for 1000 [[gp]], including [[Free Account]] players.

He's the magistrate of [[Fibula]].<br>
People do not tend to buy the key from him as it can be bought more cheaply from [[Simon the Beggar]]. <br>
{{JSpoiler|Involved in the [[Postman Quest]].}}

His full name is Pydar Firefist, [[son of Fire]], from the [[Savage Axes]].<br />
He is the head [[Pyromancer NPCs|Pyromancer]] of [[Kazordoon]]. He knows a lot about other [[Kazordoon NPCs]].<br />
{{JSpoiler|He gives you the second part (''the mark of the flame'') of [[The Spark of the Phoenix]] [[blessing]]; the first part is provided by [[Kawill]]. If you have completed [[The Paradox Tower Quest]] and bring a [[Phoenix Egg]] with you, Pydar will charge you 10% less.}}

It is living with [[Lothar]] as its friend.
{{Infobox Transcript|
''Player'': '''Arkarra'''<br/>
Lothar: The [[stampor]] in the back? She's my friend, but she came to me out of her own free will. I must admit I've never managed to tame any other stampor. ...<br />
Lothar: I heard that there's some sort of voodoo magic which would allow you to summon a stampor, but I'm not a voodoo expert, so I wouldn't know.
}}

Bozo tells [[Bozo Jokes|funny jokes]] about many [[creatures]] and has interesting comments about his fellow [[Thais NPCs|Thaians]]. When asked about his job as the Royal Jester, he stops mid-sentence to claim he is the tax collector and asks if you want to pay your taxes.
When asked about weapons, he'll sell you the "[[Mace of the Fury]]" (a [[Rolling Pin]] for 250 [[gp]]), and when asked about magic, he'll ask if you'd like to learn the spell "Lessen Your Load" for 200 gp (and gives you nothing).<br />
He can be related to [[Rookgaard]] since there is a grave on the premium side that says:<br />
:{{Message|type=look|You see a sign.<br />You read: Bozo<br />Jester and escape artist}}
Bozo is a clear [[Allusions#Bozo the Clown|allusion]] to [[wikipedia:Bozo the Clown|Bozo the Clown]], usually shortened to "Bozo" in real life.
{{JSpoiler|Main [[NPC]] of the [[What a Foolish Quest]].}}

