{{Transport |Ab'Dendriel, 70 |Ankrahmun, 160 |Carlin, 110 |Cormaya, 20 |Liberty Bay, 170 |Oramond, 110;Rank of "Citizen" in the [[Rathleton Quest]] required.|Port Hope, 150 |Thais, 160 |Venore, 40}}

He can also transport anyone to the [[Character World Transfer|world transfer]] island [[Travora]] for 1000 [[gp]], including [[Free Account]] players.

The [[Defiler]]-shaped King of the [[Orcs]]. His real name is Charkahn the Slayer.  His appearance as a [[Defiler]] was caused by a curse casted upon him by a [[Djinn]].<br>
'''Warning:''' The first time you say 'hi' to him, he will summon 3 [[Orc Leader]]s, 2 [[Orc Warlord]]s and 3 [[Slime]]s. A possible strategy is to stand on his [[Throne]] when saying hi (instead of running south), this way you can be melee attacked by a maximum of 3 creatures.<br />[[File:Orc King Strategy.png|thumb|300px]]<br />
{{JSpoiler|
Part of [[The Djinn War - Efreet Faction]] / [[The Djinn War - Marid Faction]].<br />
Part of [[What a Foolish Quest]], mission 10.
}}

She will only talk to you if you are able to speak the language of wolves, otherwise she will only say GRRRRRRRRRRRRR. Her real name is '''Faolan''', as said by [[Ceiron]] who refers to her as the Great Wolf Mother.
<br />
{{JSpoiler|
The language of wolves can be learnt from [[Ceiron]]. <br>
She is the NPC for the last step of the [[Druid Outfits Quest]]. She will grant you the final reward of the [[Druid Outfits Quest]].
}}

