[[File:AssaStars.GIF|right|Way to Atrad]]
He will only speak with you if you have the [[Assassin Outfit]] (addons are '''not''' needed) and if you are on fire. He can be found North from the hole you come up. In addition, you have to be level 80 or higher to buy assassin stars.
{{JSpoiler|Part of the [[Assassin Outfits Quest]].}}

The Blind Prophet speaks out a strong warning against going anywhere near the [[Forbidden Lands]]. Ask him for a ''transport'' if you want to go there and are worthy.<br>
Looks the same as a [[Merlkin]].
{{JSpoiler|Part of [[The Ape City Quest]].}}

His full name is Talphion Sparkbender, [[son of the Machine]], from the [[Savage Axes]].<br />
Talphion is a Technomancer that resides in [[Kazordoon]], he wants to create a clock for the [[Colossus]] in the near future. Due to the noises the machine of his makes, it's difficult for him to hear you well. For example, if you say "[[Kazordoon]]", he responds with "WHAT?", if you say it again, he'll ask "WHO'S DOOMED?" and if you say if a third time, he'll finally understand you.
{{JSpoiler|If you bring him the [[Screwdriver of Kurik]], he will reward you with a Steampowered Spikesword.<br />
Players are also required to talk with him while doing the [[The Postman Missions Quest]], mission 6.
}}
[[File:Talphion.jpg|thumb|A map.]]

Along with [[Silfind]], Hjaern is an extremely adept to the spirit arts. He teaches [[Druid#Spells|Druid Spells]].<br />
{{JSpoiler|
Part of [[The Ice Islands Quest]].
Part of [[What a Foolish Quest]], mission 10.
}}

Malor was once a general of the [[Djinn]] under [[Gabel]], but an ancient incident split the Djinn into their now separate factions. Malor and his [[Efreet]] and [[Green Djinn]] live with a great amount of anger and a sense of vengeance. They are also driven by a desire for eventual world domination.
{{JSpoiler|Part of [[The Djinn War - Efreet Faction]].<br />
Part of [[Killing in the Name of... Quest]].}}

He is the hermit that lives on the top of a mountain in [[Drefia]]. He provides information about the life of an assassin and NPC's involved in getting the assassin outfit and its addons. He was once an assassin, but is now old and retired.<br/>
Go up {{Mapper Coords|129.66|126.194|7|3|text=here}}, walk north and west and go up a ramp, walk west and north until you see a cave with a hole down. Levitate up on the left side of the cave, there lives Samir.
{{JSpoiler|Part of the [[Assassin Outfits Quest]].}}

This [[NPC]] is located at the end of the [[Pits of Inferno Quest]], just before you use [[Key 3700]] to access the reward room. He seems to be interested in trading something - something you usually wouldn't bring to the [[Pits of Inferno]].<br />
{{JSpoiler|He wants [[God Flowers]]. After you give them to him he will give you a hint on how to get [[Key 3700]], which is needed to enter the reward room.<br />
He will teleport you out of the [[Pits of Inferno]]'s main room if you say "teleport" to him. You will arrive in the [[Slime]] cave under the [[Plains of Havoc]].}}

It seems he's the chief of the [[Nargor]] pirates and the owner of the tavern. He also gambles. You can bet from 1 to 99 gold and if the [[Die]] lands on 6 you get 5 times your bet. You may also bet 100 gp for a chance to win the Die. Similar to the main money gambling game, if the Die lands on 6 you will win it. He often ends his sentences with ''Har Har Har''.<br />
Klaus is an allusion to [[wikipedia:Klaus Badelt|Klaus Badelt]], composer of music to ''Pirates of the Caribbean: The Curse of the Black Pearl''.
{{JSpoiler|Part of the [[Meriana Quest]] and the [[Treasure Hunt Quest]].}}

Representative of the [[Explorer Society]].
{{JSpoiler|
Part of [[The Explorer Society Quest]].<br />
Part of [[The New Frontier Quest]].
}}

Adrenius is a priest of [[Fafnar]]. Before the [[Desert Dungeon Quest]] got completely spoiled, this NPC was a important part of the puzzle.<br>'''Adrenius''' wrote the book [[Dangers of Adventures Critique Adrenius (Book)]].<br />
{{JSpoiler|He is very angry at [[Netlios]]'s books. He will test your knowledge about the books he wrote for 500 [[gp]]. If you say "yes" but don't have 500 gp with you, he will cast [[Soulfire]] on you, damaging you for 10 hitpoints per turn for 45 turns (450 damage total). If you are around level 15, and have [[food]] with you, this should be enough to survive. If you do have the money with you and pass the test, you will earn [[Key 4023]]. 

<br>''Transcriptions''<br>"Hi",<br>"Netlios",<br>"yes",<br>"yes",<br>"anaso, 41, attacked by mother-bear, 117 days",<br>"elaeus, 39, attacked by dragon, 100 days",<br>"gadinius, 42, stepped in fire, 83 days",<br>"heso, 40, attacked by troll, 66 days",<br>"hestus, 38, drank poison, 134 days".
}}

Captain Jack is a friend of [[Dalbrect]]. He provides passages back to the [[Tibia (Continent)|mainland]]. To return to the mainland, you need to be allowed to do so from [[Costello]], and then you can successfully say "Tibia" to Captain Jack.

If you entered the third floor of the monastery he will not transport you back until you've paid the fine.

{{NPC Quote|Captain Jack|By the gods! You must be that intruder the good brothers were talking about! Begone!}}

