Lora handed out a small gift to every [[character]] based on its age (creation date) during [[Tibia's 20th Anniversary|Tibia's 20<sup>th</sup> Anniversary]] (although characters created less than one year ago received nothing). These gifts were as follows:
*1–2 years: 2 [[Blue Surprise Bag]]s;
*2–3 years: 3 [[Blue Surprise Bag]]s;
*3–4 years: 1 [[Red Surprise Bag]];
*4–5 years: 2 [[Red Surprise Bag]]s;
*5 years and older: 3 [[Red Surprise Bag]]s.

Riddler was a man who sought to learn the secret of death and become a god. He built the [[Paradox Tower]] that includes a [[Paradox Tower Library|library]] and a challenge on most floors to get to the next one. He eventually died but his ghost still guards the tower and will reward those who answer his mad questions correctly.<br/>
Riddler may have been the man, [[Porgol]], who was an apprentice to [[Arcian]] whom he betrayed. He sought to become a great necromancer and killed his master in trying to gain power.<br />
{{JSpoiler|Part of [[The Paradox Tower Quest]].}}

King Tibianus is the sixth king of [[Kingdom of Thais|the Thaian kingdom]], after succeeding his father [[Xenom]]. He is a direct descendant of [[Banor]], the first human. King Tibianus has the power to [[Promotion|promote]] worthy adventurers. Greet him by saying ''Hail (to the beloved) King'' or ''Hello King'' or else he will ignore you. If you swear at him his guards will attack you leaving you with only 1 [[Hitpoint]]. He claims to buy the [[Excalibug]], though its existence is unproven. His dog [[Noodles]] is known as the best sniffer dog in the kingdom.<br>
He may be an [[Allusions|allusion]] to the roman emperor Tiberius III. 
{{JSpoiler|Part of the [[Isle of Evil Quest]] and [[The New Frontier Quest]]. He also gives you a [[Dog Collar|leash]] as part of the [[Noodles is Gone Mini World Change]].}}

'''Leeland Slim''' runs the [[Useful Things Warehouse]].<br />
His name [[Allusions|references]] Stephen Kings' book/movie [[wikipedia:Needful Things|Needful Things]] where the main villian known as "Leland Gaunt" owns a shop called Needful Things.<br />
{{JSpoiler|Part of [[The New Frontier Quest]], mission 5.}}

His full name is Kawill Marbleeye, [[son of Earth]], from the [[Molten Rock]].<br />
He works as Geomancer Chief for the [[Dwarven Empire]].<br />
{{JSpoiler|He gives you the first part (''the life-giving earth'') of [[The Spark of the Phoenix]] [[blessing]]; the second part is provided by [[Pydar]].}}

{{Transport|discount=no
 |Isle of the Kings, 10; become his friend 
